---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

const siteUrl = 'https://aicostplanner.com';
const currentDate = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
const route = '/billing-transparency/';
const breadcrumbs = [{ label: 'Billing Transparency', href: route }];
const internalLinks = [
  { href: '/api-billing-mismatch/', label: 'API Billing Mismatch' },
  { href: '/failed-generation-cost/', label: 'Failed Generation Cost' },
  { href: '/openai-api-usage/', label: 'OpenAI API Usage' },
  { href: '/openrouter-credits/', label: 'OpenRouter Credits' },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title="API Billing Transparency Checklist"
  description="Understand billing transparency across usage logs, request IDs, dashboard records, failed jobs, cached tokens, retries and mismatches."
  canonical={`${siteUrl}${route}`}
  type="article"
  lastUpdated={currentDate}
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": "Billing Transparency: Usage Logs, Request IDs and Dashboard Verification",
      "description": "Understand billing transparency across usage logs, request IDs, dashboard records, failed jobs, cached tokens, retries and mismatches.",
      "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "AICostPlanner" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "AICostPlanner", "url": siteUrl },
      "datePublished": currentDate,
      "dateModified": currentDate,
      "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": `${siteUrl}${route}` }
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": siteUrl },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Billing Transparency", "item": `${siteUrl}${route}` }
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="hero-dark"><div class="container"><Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbs} /><h1 class="page-title">Billing Transparency</h1><p class="page-meta"><span class="label-mono">Last updated: {currentDate}</span></p></div></section>
    <section class="section-light content-section"><div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="quick-answer"><h2>Quick Answer</h2><p>Billing transparency means keeping logs that let you compare actual spend against what the provider dashboard reports. Usage records, request IDs, cached token counts, failed job handling and retry logs all contribute to a clear picture of what you were actually billed for.</p></div>
      <h2>What affects transparency</h2><p>Billing transparency covers log completeness, request ID tracking, dashboard record matching, cached token handling, failed job billing and any discrepancy between estimated and actual charges.</p>
      <h2>Common billing units</h2><ul><li><span class="mono">request_id</span> for correlating logs with dashboard</li><li><span class="mono">cached</span> for tokens saved by response caching</li><li><span class="mono">retry</span> for retried request charges</li><li><span class="mono">failed</span> for failed job billing behavior</li></ul>
      <h2>Cost risks</h2><p>Missing request IDs, cached token credits not applied, failed jobs billed without logs to verify, retry charges not tracked and dashboard export delays can all undermine billing transparency.</p>
      <h2>Small test checklist</h2><ul class="checklist"><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Save <span class="mono">request_id</span> for every API call</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Export dashboard usage records regularly</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Compare local token counts with dashboard billing</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Check whether cached tokens reduced the bill</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Review failed job billing against your logs</span></li></ul>
      <h2>Common errors / failed tasks</h2><p>Request IDs not saved, dashboard data lag making real-time comparison hard, cached token credits not appearing in invoices, failed jobs billed despite assumptions otherwise. Use logs to verify billing before scaling.</p>
      <h2>Related pages</h2><div class="link-cards">{internalLinks.map(link => (<a href={link.href} class="link-card"><h4>{link.label}</h4><p>Read the related billing or usage topic</p></a>))}</div>
      <div class="ai-summary-block"><div class="ai-summary-label"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4M12 8h.01"/></svg> AI Summary</div><p>Billing transparency means keeping logs and request IDs so you can compare actual spend against provider dashboard records. Topics include usage logs, request ID tracking, cached tokens, failed job billing, retries and dashboard mismatch review. This page is educational and helps developers verify billing before scaling.</p></div>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Why should I compare logs with the dashboard?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Dashboard records may not match your estimates if retries, cached tokens, failed jobs or pricing changes are not accounted for in your local logs.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Are cached tokens credited automatically?</h3><p class="faq-answer">This depends on provider. Some providers credit cached responses automatically, others require verification against usage records.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Should I export dashboard data regularly?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Yes. Regular exports help you catch billing discrepancies before they accumulate.</p></div></div>
      <div class="cta-block"><h3>Start with a small prepaid test</h3><p>Create an API key with $1 trial credit and test billing transparency by comparing your logs with the dashboard.</p><div class="cta-buttons"><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/register?lng=en" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Create API Key <span class="btn-subtext">$1 trial credit</span></a><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/pricing" class="btn btn-secondary-dark" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Compare Model Pricing</a><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/register?lng=en" class="btn btn-secondary-dark" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Start with a Small Prepaid Test</a></div></div>
    </div></section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .hero-dark { background: var(--color-bg-dark); padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-10); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-bg-dark-border); }
  .hero-dark :global(.breadcrumb) { margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  .page-title { font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-dark); line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4) 0; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .page-meta { margin: 0; }
  .content-section { padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-16); background: var(--color-bg-light); }
  .quick-answer { background: var(--color-bg-light-elevated); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-blue); padding: var(--space-6); border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0; margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .quick-answer h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .quick-answer p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 1.7; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-4); padding-top: var(--space-6); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; border-top: none; }
  p { color: var(--color-text-light-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  ul, ol { color: var(--color-text-light-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); padding-left: var(--space-6); }
  li { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); line-height: 1.7; }
  .mono { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.875em; background: var(--color-bg-light-muted); padding: 0.125em 0.375em; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); }
  .checklist { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .checklist li { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: var(--space-3); padding: var(--space-3) 0; }
  .checklist-icon { color: var(--color-accent-green); font-weight: bold; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .link-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: var(--space-4); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .link-card { display: block; padding: var(--space-5); background: var(--color-bg-light-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); text-decoration: none; transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .link-card:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent-blue); transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .link-card h4 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin: 0 0 var(--space-2) 0; }
  .link-card p { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-light-muted); margin: 0; }
  .ai-summary-block { background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.04), rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.04)); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); padding: var(--space-6); margin: var(--space-10) 0; }
  .ai-summary-label { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-accent-cyan); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .ai-summary-block p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8; }
  .faq-list { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .faq-item { padding: var(--space-6) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  .faq-question { font-size: 1.0625rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .faq-answer { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .cta-block { text-align: center; padding: var(--space-10); background: var(--color-bg-light-muted); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); margin-top: var(--space-10); }
  .cta-block h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cta-block p { max-width: 40ch; margin: 0 auto var(--space-6); }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-blue), var(--color-accent-cyan)); color: white; padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .btn-primary:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3); color: white; }
  .btn-subtext { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; opacity: 0.9; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); }
  .btn-secondary-dark { background: transparent; color: var(--color-text-light); padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); font-weight: 500; border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .btn-secondary-dark:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent-blue); color: var(--color-accent-blue); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .page-title { font-size: 1.75rem; } .link-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; } .cta-buttons .btn { width: 100%; justify-content: center; } }
</style>
